@page "/"
@* Home Page - Landing page for the Clubs Management application *@

<PageTitle>Home - Clubs Management</PageTitle>

<div class="home-container">
    <h1>Clubs Management System</h1>
    <h3>A02: Clubs Assignment</h3>

    <div class="info-section">
        <h4>üìã Assignment Information</h4>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Student Name:</strong> [Your Name Here]</li>
            <li><strong>Assignment:</strong> A02 - Clubs (Query and CRUD Components)</li>
            <li><strong>Last Modified:</strong> @DateTime.Now.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="features-section">
        <h4>‚ú® Features Implemented</h4>
        <div class="feature-grid">
            <div class="feature-card">
                <h5>üîç Query Component</h5>
                <p>Search and display clubs by active status with pagination support</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Filter by Active/Inactive status</li>
                    <li>Display club ID, name, staff, and fee</li>
                    <li>Tabular results with pagination</li>
                    <li>Shows "No staff member" when applicable</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="feature-card">
                <h5>‚úèÔ∏è CRUD Component</h5>
                <p>Complete Create, Read, Update, and Deactivate operations for clubs</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Create new clubs with validation</li>
                    <li>Update existing club information</li>
                    <li>Deactivate/Reactivate clubs (soft delete)</li>
                    <li>Employee dropdown with filtered staff</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="business-rules-section">
        <h4>üìù Business Rules Implemented</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>‚úÖ Club entries are deactivated, not deleted</li>
            <li>‚úÖ Reactivation button available for inactive clubs</li>
            <li>‚úÖ Employee dropdown shows only: Instructors, Office Administrators, Technical Support</li>
            <li>‚úÖ ClubID must be unique (Primary Key)</li>
            <li>‚úÖ Club names must be unique</li>
            <li>‚úÖ Club fees cannot be negative</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="queries-section">
        <h4>üîé Required Queries Implemented</h4>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Employee Club List:</strong> Ordered list of employees associated with clubs (by last name)</li>
            <li><strong>Club by Status:</strong> Ordered list of clubs by active status (by club name)</li>
            <li><strong>Club by ID:</strong> Retrieve a specific club by its ID</li>
            <li><strong>Available Staff:</strong> Employees in eligible positions (by last name)</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

    <div class="tech-stack-section">
        <h4>üõ†Ô∏è Technology Stack</h4>
        <div class="tech-grid">
            <div class="tech-item">
                <strong>.NET 9.0</strong>
                <p>Blazor Server</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tech-item">
                <strong>Entity Framework Core</strong>
                <p>ORM & Data Access</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tech-item">
                <strong>SQL Server</strong>
                <p>Database</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tech-item">
                <strong>Bootstrap 5</strong>
                <p>UI Framework</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="known-bugs-section">
        <h4>üêõ Known Issues</h4>
        <p>None currently identified. All features tested and working as expected.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="credits-section">
        <h4>üôè Credits & Attributions</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Assignment provided by NAIT - DMIT1517 Course</li>
            <li>Based on WestWind solution architecture patterns</li>
            <li>Bootstrap framework for styling</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</div>

